        "Description": "libblur is a high-performance, pure Rust library dedicated to image blurring. It provides a variety of production-ready blur algorithms (including Gaussian, Stack, Box, and Median blur) with deep optimizations for SIMD instruction sets (NEON, SSE, AVX). It is particularly well-suited for real-time image processing tasks on both desktop and embedded platforms."
